headline: Rollins (ROL): Reassessing Valuation After Record Q3 Results and a Barclays Rating Upgrade
summary: Rollins (ROL) just delivered a record third quarter and followed it up with a rating upgrade from Barclays, a one two punch that has pushed the stock sharply higher in recent weeks. See our latest analysis for Rollins. Those record Q3 numbers and the Barclays upgrade seem to have reinforced an already strong story, with the share price now at $61.4 and a year to date share price return of roughly one third.
